    "discriminators": [
     "Struck metal that rings: a fast attack followed by a long, strongly INHARMONIC decaying tail. Inharmonicity is the whole call — a cast bell's partials sit near 2.0, 2.4, 3.0 and 4.2 times the hum, not at integers.",
     "ALARMS-BUZZER holds a continuous, harmonically dense drive and never decays; ALARMS-ELECTRONIC is a near-pure synthetic tone with almost no inharmonicity. A bell is the only alarm mechanism here that is struck.",
     "ALARMS-SIREN sweeps; a bell's partials are fixed in frequency.",
     "Alarm function (repeated strikes, warning context) rather than the single musical strike of BELLS-LARGE or BELLS-HANDBELL, which are otherwise the same object."
    ],
