    "discriminators": [
     "A rasp, not a ring: sustained, low-crest, flat-topped drive with a dense odd-harmonic comb — high total_harmonic_distortion and a high partial_count are the signature. The energy is held, so sustain_ratio is high and decay time is near zero.",
     "ALARMS-BELL is impulsive with a long inharmonic tail; the buzzer has no tail because it is never struck.",
     "ALARMS-ELECTRONIC is the opposite spectrum: a near-sinusoid, very low spectral_flatness, few partials, low distortion. Buzzer = many partials and dirty; electronic = few partials and clean.",
     "A rasping door buzzer belongs here; a mechanical ding-dong doorbell is BELLS-DOORBELL."
    ],
