    "discriminators": [
     "The repeating pulse train is the cue: high onset_periodicity at a few hits per second. A single held tone is ALARMS-ELECTRONIC; a single inharmonic ring is ALARMS-BELL.",
     "UCS puts BOTH digital (piezo beeping) and analog (bell-striking) clock alarms here, so the subcategory deliberately spans two morphologies and DSP cannot finish the call. The words clock, alarm, snooze, timer or wind in the name are the deciding evidence.",
     "Clock mechanism ticking without an alarm is CLOCKS-TICK; a chiming clock is CLOCKS-CHIME."
