    "discriminators": [
     "A synthetic near-pure tone: very high harmonicity, very low spectral_flatness, very few partials, almost no inharmonicity, and usually pulsed rather than continuous (smoke-detector chirp, keypad alert), so onset_periodicity is high.",
     "ALARMS-BUZZER is the spectral inverse — a dense, distorted harmonic comb. Buzzer is dirty and many-partialled; electronic is clean and few-partialled.",
     "No inharmonic decaying tail, which rules out ALARMS-BELL. No frequency sweep, which rules out ALARMS-SIREN.",
     "Car alarms are acoustically identical but go to VEHICLES-ALARM by UCS rule, so the name must decide between the two."
    ],
